    "tags": ["US-China tariffs", "Iran ceasefire", "Islamabad talks", "AI model theft", "Hormuz", "European energy"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 10, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 📦 US and China Are Now Taxing Each Other Into Bilateral Silence\n\nOn April 10, US tariffs on Chinese imports reached 145%. China responded with 125%. At these rates, trade economists say bilateral trade has effectively ceased.\n\n- **The escalation:** Trump raised tariffs by 50 additional points on April 9, bringing the US rate to 145%. China matched with 125%. The Supreme Court killed Trump's \"reciprocal\" tariff authority in February, so this round runs on alternative legal mechanisms whose constitutional durability is unclear.\n- **The summit:** A Trump-Xi meeting is scheduled for May. The two sides are taxing each other into silence while planning a cordial diplomatic photo opportunity.\n\n*145% on one side, 125% on the other. The May summit is going to be a lovely afternoon.*\n\n**Sources:** [Tax Foundation](https://taxfoundation.org/research/all/federal/trump-tariffs-trade-war/) | [Time](https://time.com/7325306/us-china-trump-xi-trade-tensions-truce-export-controls-tariffs/)\n\n---\n\n## 🕊️ Iran and the US Have a Ceasefire. Iran Says the US Already Broke It.\n\nThe ceasefire is 48 hours old. Iran's parliamentary speaker has accused the US of violating three of its ten provisions. JD Vance is flying to Islamabad anyway.\n\n- **The accusation:** Mohammad Bagher Ghalibaf says the US violated three clauses of the 10-point plan Trump accepted as a basis for negotiation. The Strait of Hormuz — which was supposed to reopen — remains \"effectively closed.\"\n- **Islamabad:** Vice President JD Vance is leading the US delegation to Friday talks in Pakistan. Trump has indicated a nuclear deal is the endgame. Iran's conditions include control of the Strait and lifting all sanctions.\n\n*Two days into the ceasefire, one party says the other already cheated. Talks are in Islamabad. Normal Friday.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/08/ceasefire-iran-war-lebanon.html) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/8/iran-says-talks-with-us-will-begin-in-pakistans-islamabad-on-friday) | [CNN](https://www.cnn.com/2026/04/08/middleeast/us-iran-ceasefire-explainer-war-intl-hnk)\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 The Frontier Labs Built Walls. China Built 24,000 Keys.\n\nOpenAI, Google, and Anthropic discovered Chinese AI firms were systematically harvesting their model outputs through 24,000 fraudulent accounts to train competing systems.\n\n- **The operation:** Anthropic documented 16 million exchanges from DeepSeek, Moonshot AI, and MiniMax — all via fraudulently created accounts. The three labs are now sharing intelligence through the Frontier Model Forum to detect and block future attempts.\n- **The technique:** \"Adversarial distillation\" — using a frontier model's outputs to train a cheaper competing system. Against terms of service. Also, apparently, how you build a competitive LLM without the $25B R&D budget.\n\n*Nobody could have predicted that selling API access to the world's best AI would create a training-data problem.*\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-06/openai-anthropic-google-unite-to-combat-model-copying-in-china) | [TechBrew](https://www.techbrew.com/stories/openai-anthropic-google-distillation-collab)\n\n---\n\n## ⛽ Hormuz Is Still Closed. European Airports Are Rationing Jet Fuel.\n\nThe ceasefire technically included a Hormuz reopening. Iran has \"limited the number of ships that can cross.\" European energy infrastructure is adjusting its definition of fine.\n\n- **The situation:** European gas storage is at 30% capacity after a harsh winter. Dutch TTF benchmarks have nearly doubled. Airports are rationing jet fuel; airlines are proactively canceling flights. The last Hormuz shipments are reaching European ports this week.\n- **The deadline:** Russian envoy Kirill Dmitriev puts complete fuel depletion at April 20. The IEA called the closure \"the largest supply disruption in the history of the global oil market.\" The ceasefire bought two weeks. The fuel doesn't care.\n\n*(Fine. Probably fine.)*\n\n**Sources:** [Euronews](https://www.euronews.com/business/2026/04/09/why-oil-and-gas-prices-could-stay-high-in-europe-even-if-the-iran-war-ends) | [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Iran_war_fuel_crisis) | [Time](https://time.com/article/2026/04/05/strait-of-hormuz-fuel-rationing-oil/)"
  }
]
